#12507
Atop the Inner Walls~
   Pacing about the heights of the inner wall offers no respite from the pall
that lingers heavily about the keep.  The air here, as elsewhere, is heavy and
still, almost as though even the most lighthearted breezes would steer cleer of
these hills.  Perhaps worse yet, when the occassional wind blows across the
keep's crenelated battlements it creates a gale of sound most disturbing, from
a low mournful breeze to a shieking wail of wind that seems to echo the
desolation of this forgotten place.  A shallow trough runs along the exterior
edge of the floor of the wall.  Now clogged with debris and filth, these
troughs look to have once fed the leering gargoyles that grace the exterior of
the inner wall here near to the entryway below.    
