#12508
Before an Enormous Cauldron~
   An enormous cauldron rests here precariously amid the remains of the
castle's battlements.  The remains of a fire pit can be seen nearby,
accompanied by a few scattered and rusting metal fragments of what was likely a
mounting device for the cauldron, now long destroyed by the elements and age.
Along the exterior of the inner wall are several wickedly leering faces of
grotesque sculpture, a fine cadre of gargoyles to warn any foolhardy enough
have beseiged these walls in their days of glory.  A shallow gathering pool
rests to the exterior side of the wall, feeding in turn a shallow trough that
stretches away to the north and south.  Further passage south along this route
has been effectively sealed off by the collapse of the massive cauldron.    
