#12509
Walking the Battlements~
   While not as tall as several keeps of the age to which it belonged, the
walls of this forgotten fortress tower yet above the surrounding countryside,
lending a slight sense of vertigo to those not accustomed to heights.  The
slight dizziness afforded by the heights is oddly furthered by the usual lack
of wind of any kind, a stifling pall that hangs heavy over the surrounding
lands.  Worse yet is the keening created by the faltering battlements when the
rare breeze does cross this land.  Ranging from a low, mournful wail, the
lament of the keep is made all the more palpable as the wind increases to a
shrieking scream as it runs from the desolation of these hills.    
