#12515
Within A Small Tower~
   A short guardtower rests here at the corner of the keep's walls, it's squat
structure even shorter now that the eastern side has collapsed completely upon
itself.  In a time of ages passed, the building would have seemed sturdy and
quite readily defensible, barred by thick, oaken doors reinforced with banded
iron.  Now, however, one such door hanges ajar, knocked free from it's moorings
through it's battle with the elements and the ages.  The brief glance afforded
within is not entirely enlightening, but offers testament to the usual defenses
as murder holes, or arrow slits, used by the keep's defenders, peer out about
the region below.  An odd addition, the remains of a large ballista have
collapsed along with the remainder of the roof, the remnants of what can only
be described as a massive, barbed grappling hook yet set in its breech.    
