#12549
A Crumbling, Stone Landing~
   Passing through the aged stone archway finds one upon a darkened landing of
natural stone.  Once polished smooth and blanketed in decorative rugs, this
wide landing is now as lost to time as the remainder of the keep.  Dust settles
thick upon the now dull stonework, while thick layers of spiderwebs now drape
the walls as the rotted and frayed rug once did the floor.  Upon the left a
narrow stair spirals into darkness, while, perhaps unbelievably, a light seems
to come from the top of a wide stair upon the right.    
