At the Foot of the Stair~
   At the foot of this narrow stairwell rests an equally narrow corridor,
flanked here by twin alcoves where one can easily imagine twin sentries
standing at attention.  Cobwebs hang heavy and thick here in the darkness,
anchored to wrought iron sconces long since devoid of the light of torch.  
Dank and wet, this lower hall has little in the ways of ammenities and looks to
have ever been as such, although certainly it was once far more agreeable than
it now appears.  Smelling of must and mildew, and of something else less easily
defined, this corridor almost seems to prefer being forgotten, as even light
introduced to the area seems somehow diminished.    
