A Cramped Guardroom~
   Forcing passed the warping of the wooden door requires little effort, yet
offers equally as little in reward.  Greated with a cloud of ages old dust, the
room becomes momentarily obscured.  As the dust settles, the form of a cramped
and austere guardsroom is made evident.  Draped thickly in spiderwebs, little
appears to have disturbed this room in ages.  A simple desk, set high from the
floor, is accompanied by a strict-looking, straight-backed chair.  Resting
against the southern wall is a sturdy weapons rack, locked and barred by a
wrought iron grate.    
