A Suit of Battered and Bloodied Plate~
   This appears to have once been the showcase of the keep's coffers, marked by
the absence of chests and containers that may have at one time held defining
wealth in coins or jewels.  Instead, this would have had, in ages long since
lost, the trapings of artwork and statue, more aesthetic treasures to display,
their value more fluid but capable of far greater heights.  None of these
precious items yet remain, however, and even the decorative displays and cases
have been toppled and shattered, strewn about as if in fury and left to lay in
either haste or apathy.  In the place of these lost prizes rest a new, solitary
centerpiece.  Standing upon a yet sturdy support, perhaps an image of an age
and lord long gone, is a suit of damaged Solamnic Plate, a gift given a knight
of that realm on their lordship to their order.    
